metadata.name: The Hum of Cyber Forest #72
metadata.description:
The forest exists as a noise, a hum of ever-changing states. 
The forest is chaos. 
The forest is technological, as it is filled with an uninterrupted seething of information, the exchange of pollen dust.

The rhythmic song of a cyborg shaman mingling with this noise evokes disintegrating, pixelated visions.

Rhythms of tree trunks are made with a help of DALL¬∑E mini neural network and were inspired by surrealistic painters.
Thanks Yulikolay for helping. The dithering code was inspired by a number of examples, links to which are indicated in the work‚Äôs code.

metadata.name: Tesseract Visions #120
metadata.description:
Tesseract Visions is an abstract generative artwork inspired by the movie Interstellar.

''The Tesseract is an enormous, hyper-cubic, grid-like structure and a means of communication for the bulk beings to express action through gravity with NASA. The bulk beings can perceive five dimensions instead of four, able to see every moment in the past, present, and future. The bulk beings can influence gravity within any of those time frames.''
(https://interstellarfilm.fandom.com/wiki/Tesseract)

The work presents the observation of the universe from a tesseract. I tried to symbolize the past through form of sketches and drawings, the present with a current view inside the Tesseract, and the future with the occasional showing of supernovas and black holes in some iterations.

It's amazing how far we've come as a human race, from sketching with charcoal to coding, from walking through the desert to traveling through space.

I hope that this chaotic collection will make sense to you despite its illogicality.


Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 'd' to save a hi-res PNG image

Created using p5.js
Bajiru, July 2023.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #539
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.name: When we were Kids #5
metadata.description:
When we were kids.

A work that goes back to our childhood.
When I was a kid I loved spending time with my grandmother and parents, we took a lot of walks with them, looked at different houses, spent time in nature, painted and in general were very much involved in the creative component, it was my parents and grandmother who instilled in me a love for creativity.

Probably one of the few things that have survived to these days is my childhood drawings, a little funny, sloppy, but so real and sincere.

In this work I wanted to take me back to those carefree times and remember with what eagerness and zeal I tried every day to learn something new or to go further than before.

None of this would have happened without my family, for which I am truly grateful.

10% of primary sales will be donated to Cure Parkinson's, I hope all children will have a childhood where they can spend time with their loved ones.

Be patient, some variations take a little longer to render.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.
